verbose_text: However, lufenuron administered orally at the dose recommended for flea control (i.e. between about 30 and 133 mg/kg) did not prevent cats from becoming infected with dermatophytosis after direct topical challenge with M. canis [XREF_BIBR] or after contact with other infected cats [XREF_BIBR].
